        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the rope: a) ligature mark; b) abrasion; c) bruise; d) pressure abrasion; e) strangulation; f) hanging; g) friction burns due to dragging.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Incised wound. 2) Chop wound. 3) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Commonly used for homicidal ligature strangulation. • Frequently used for suicidal hanging. • Accidental injuries may occur during occupational activities or accidental entanglement. • The ligature mark and its pattern may help identify the type of rope used and aid in reconstruction of the manner of death. Name of weapon: ROPE"
