        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the sharp blades: a) incised wound; b) stab wound; c) penetrating wound; d) perforating wound. • By the pointed tips: punctured wound, injury to internal organs. • By the handles: abrasion, bruise, lacerated wound.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Chop wound. 2) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Commonly encountered in homicidal assaults. • Suicidal injuries may occasionally be produced, particularly stab wounds. • Accidental injuries are common during domestic, tailoring, and occupational use. • The wound characteristics may help in identifying the use of scissors as the causative weapon. Name of weapon: SCISSOR"
