        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the sharp edge: a) incised wound; b) cut wound. • By the pointed tip: a) stab wound; b) penetrating wound; c) perforating wound; d) injury to internal organs. • By the handle: abrasion, bruise, lacerated wound.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Chop wound. 2) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Commonly used for homicidal assaults. • Suicidal injuries may occasionally be encountered. • Accidental injuries may occur during domestic, occupational, or recreational use. Name of weapon: HINGE KNIFE"
