        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the weight plates: a) abrasion; b) bruise; c) lacerated wound; d) fracture of bones; e) crush injuries; f) rupture of internal organs following severe blows. • By the handle: abrasion, bruise, lacerated wound.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Incised wound. 2) Stab wound. 3) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • May be used for homicidal assaults, particularly causing severe head injuries. • Accidental injuries may occur during weight training or improper handling. • Rarely can be used for suicidal purpose. Name of weapon: DUMBBELL"
