        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the grinding stone or hand stone: a) abrasion; b) bruise; c) lacerated wound; d) fracture of bones; e) crush injuries; f) rupture of internal organs following severe blows.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Incised wound. 2) Stab wound. 3) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Commonly used for homicidal assaults, especially in domestic settings. • Accidental injuries may occur while handling or during grinding activities. • Rarely can be used for suicidal purpose. Name of weapon: GRINDING STONE"
