        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the toothed blade: a) incised wound; b) lacerated wound with serrated margins; c) cut fractures of bones; d) amputation of fingers or limbs in severe cases. • By the blunt back of the blade or handle: abrasion, bruise, lacerated wound.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Stab wound. 2) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Commonly used for homicidal assaults and dismemberment of dead bodies. • Accidental injuries may occur during carpentry and other occupational work. • Rarely can be used for suicidal purpose. • The serrated nature of the wound may help in identifying the use of a hand saw. Name of weapon: HAND SAW"
