        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the ball: a) abrasion; b) bruise; c) lacerated wound; d) fracture of bones, especially of the facial bones; e) injury to the eye; f) rupture of internal organs following severe impact.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Incised wound. 2) Stab wound. 3) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Accidental injuries commonly occur during hockey matches and practice sessions. • May occasionally be used for homicidal or assaultive purposes when thrown with force. • Rarely can be used for suicidal purpose. Name of weapon: HOCKEY BALL"
