        "notes": "Injuries possible: • By the thread: a) abrasion; b) incised wound; c) cut laceration; d) ligature mark; e) partial or complete transection of blood vessels, nerves, tendons, or trachea in severe cases.\n\nInjuries not expected: 1) Chop wound. 2) Gunshot wound.\n\nMedicolegal importance: • Accidental injuries are common among motorcyclists, cyclists, pedestrians, and birds due to contact with the sharp thread. • May occasionally be used for homicidal or ligature strangulation. • Rarely can be used for suicidal purpose. • The characteristic linear cut injuries may help in identifying kite thread (Manja) as the causative weapon. Name of weapon: KITE THREAD"
